{"success": true, "message": "Fetched question.", "data": {"showTimer": true, "showAttemptInsight": true, "playSounds": true, "dontShowCorrectAnswerImmediately": false, "_id": "66bcbe8dae81d148616b1a38", "type": "singleCorrect", "level": 2, "category": null, "approximateTimeRequired": 120, "imageBaseUrl": null, "helperText": null, "source": "MOG", "classes": [], "exams": ["615d76e4c52ffa3c944600e1"], "subjects": ["615d708dbd4a37c4058ee5a8"], "chapters": ["615d6fed2b295b085ab6eb9d"], "topics": [], "concepts": [], "microConcepts": [], "questionLabels": [], "previousYearPapers": [{"_id": "64b850022a7d64ecd80b00ac", "title": "NEET 2010 (Screening)", "isVisible": true}], "question": {"text": "A vibration magnetometer placed in magnetic meridian has a small bar magnet. The magnet executes oscillations with a time period of $2 \\mathrm{~s}$ in earth's horizontal magnetic field of $24 \\mu \\mathrm{T}$. When a horizontal field of $18 \\mu \\mathrm{T}$ is produced opposite to the earth's field by placing a current carrying wire, the new time period of magnet will be", "image": null}, "options": [{"id": "KbHjt", "text": "$1 \\mathrm{~s}$", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}, {"id": "7PhQr", "text": "$2 \\mathrm{~s}$", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}, {"id": "reVio", "text": "$3 \\mathrm{~s}$", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}, {"id": "w9u3g", "text": "$4 \\mathrm{~s}$", "image": null, "isCorrect": true}], "correctValue": null, "solution": {"text": "The time period T of oscillation of a magnet is given by\r\n\\(T=2 \\pi \\sqrt{\\frac{I}{M B}}\\)\r\nwhere,\r\nI = Moment of inertia of the magnet about the axis of rotation\r\n\\(M=\\) Magnetic moment of the magnet\r\n\\(B=\\) Uniform magnetic field As I, B remains the same\r\n\\(\\therefore \\quad T \\propto \\frac{1}{\\sqrt{B}}\\) or \\(\\frac{T_2}{T_1}=\\sqrt{\\frac{B_1}{B_2}}\\)\r\nAccording to given problem,\r\n\\(\\begin{aligned}\r\nB_1 & =24 \\mu \\mathrm{T} \\\\\r\nB_2 & =24 \\mu \\mathrm{T}-18 \\mu \\mathrm{T}=6 \\mu \\mathrm{T} \\\\\r\nT_1 & =2 \\mathrm{~s} \\\\\r\n\\therefore \\quad T_2 & =(2 \\mathrm{~s}) \\sqrt{\\frac{(24 \\mu \\mathrm{T})}{(6 \\mu \\mathrm{T})}}=4 \\mathrm{~s}\r\n\\end{aligned}\\)", "image": null}, "videoSolution": null, "masterId": "MOGNEPYQ80294763", "numericalLowerLimit": null, "numericalUpperLimit": null, "bucket": "", "isRemoved": false, "updatedAt": "2024-09-09T09:45:24.934Z", "updated_by": "65d0c176a8f74604505ba6f6", "cpyqbSubjects": ["61bb58181213731910ea0b70", "61c055eae8ce0dc8a5c62d33", "616057750283de43c87e3e1b", "61964fe0a5a5260118868021", "61964f81a5a526011886801d", "629f39e4ac11b26562e0625b", "616057920283de43c87e3e1e", "615f0c729476412f48314dab", "61a8a2c2e8ce0dc8a5c62d2d", "629105adee9e3ae00d63352b", "629f385f263330a77be9fa7d", "616056cd0283de43c87e3e15", "616057190283de43c87e3e18", "62962075e7f8e9ac4daeafd7", "64d50bd73df7f4a7f3017f6f", "66b79b34d4b564dfab4f94cc", "678ea9a09cc79e5f592bdc11", "67fa5fef4468eb1307ceb0ad", "6807d2ad647479b8e8696479"], "cpyqbChapters": ["620ab21eb0cb1a4b0ae51f81", "6160241bbb74e5f3d79be031", "6160241c2f0f0966fa72eda6", "61c0899893881c7129ef5166", "61964c8b6b80fda17bcfe142", "6160241a32805db750457ecb", "61e7bd753f352d51145a14ad", "61964c8a0e95e2b64666258e", "61bb8218a216287d869bdc41", "616024195ad23af03d3d3bfd", "629109edc0a0e0ccb07999d8", "629621233563b93ca3bece80", "629f3a91eec7fbad4fc8fac2", "629f390c6ee39ad8a67118ee", "64eb06dd3118f713ecfef1ab", "66d5857ca75f05ee8564f7e5", "67921dab1d5b5072da5e9cf2", "680920383a10446a207fdf7c"], "cpyqbExams": ["616059d70283de43c87e3e24", "616059730283de43c87e3e22"]}}